data.description: MLS# 267388 Seeking a Peaceful Country Property? Nestled next to dryland wheat fields in Columbia County. Looking to start your own hobby farm? or continue the Crooked Fences legacy of selling garden produce and vegetables all summer long or simply grow your own groceries this 3.36 irrigated acres in the city limits of Dayton may be for you. Sitting on two parcels. Garden beds galore some with deer fences. 1024 sqft barn/shop with power, 10x20 Old Hickory shed and other out buildings. Home boast over 4300 sqft of space. New solar panels complete with new sub panel and whole house wiring. Meal preparation is a breeze in this spacious kitchen with stainless steel appliances including a propane cook stove. Winter warming wood stove adds a cozy note to great room where everyone can live a little and compliments your heat pump and furnace on those chilly days and nights. Retreat to the North end of the property where nearly an acre of land provides amazing views and tranquility, rest and relaxation becomes automatic sitting under one of the shade trees where you can enjoy the deer roaming or just relax and take in the panoramic views. Make the hike up the North Hill for a sensational experience!
